---
import ContactForm from '@components/ContactForm.astro'
import Grid from '@components/Grid.astro'
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro'
import CaseStudySectionText from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudySectionText.astro'
import CaseStudyResults from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyResults.astro'
import CaseStudyHeader from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyHeader.astro'
import CaseStudyToggleButton from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyToggleButton.astro'
import CaseStudyMetaData from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyMetaData.astro'
import CaseStudyShout from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyShout.astro'
import CaseStudyNav from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyNav.astro'
import CaseStudyImages from '@components/case-studies/case-study/CaseStudyImages.astro'

import hero from '@assets/case-studies/cyprusays/hero.webp'
import squareOne from '@assets/case-studies/cyprusays/squareOne.svg'
import squareTwo from '@assets/case-studies/cyprusays/squareTwo.webp'
import wideOne from '@assets/case-studies/cyprusays/wideOne.webp'
import wideTwo from '@assets/case-studies/cyprusays/wideTwo.webp'
---

<Layout
  title="Cyprusays Case Study"
  description="How Pixel Agency took Cyprusays' off-shore app build from rudderless to launched, set up project structures from scratch, and left the founders running delivery themselves."
>
  <article id="case-study-page">
    <CaseStudyHeader>
      <span slot="title">Cyprusays</span>
      <span slot="industry">Education, Community</span>
      <span slot="services">Consulting</span>
      <span slot="duration">4 months</span>
    </CaseStudyHeader>

    <CaseStudyToggleButton />

    <!-- Single shell: all images + summary (left pane) / all case study text (right pane) -->
    <section class="pb-12 lg:pb-18">
      <Grid>
        <div id="case-study-shell" class="case-study-shell col-span-full">
          <div class="case-study-left-pane min-w-0 overflow-hidden">
            <CaseStudyImages
              heroImage={{ src: hero }}
              summary="How Pixel Agency took Cyprusays' off-shore app build from rudderless to launched, set up project structures from scratch, and left the founders running delivery themselves."
              squareImages={[{ src: squareOne }, { src: squareTwo }]}
              wideImages={[{ src: wideOne }, { src: wideTwo }]}
            />
          </div>

          <div class="case-study-right-pane min-w-0">
            <CaseStudyShout>Empowering Cyprusays' founders to run their own project.</CaseStudyShout>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The client" noTopMargin={true}>
              <p class="">
                Cyprusays is an Australian start-up on a quietly important mission: helping the Cypriot diaspora
                reconnect with the Greek Cypriot language through a mobile app on iOS and Android. The app runs on a
                freemium model, with a free tier for casual learners and subscription tiers for users who want to go
                deeper. Their audience spans generations of Cypriot families across Australia and beyond, many of whom
                feel a piece of their heritage slipping away with each generation.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The problem">
              <p>
                Cyprusays had a clear product vision, finished designs, and an off-shore development team ready to start
                building. What they didn't have was anyone with experience setting up and running a technical project.
                They were on the cusp of kicking off the build, but with no formal requirements, no roadmap, and no idea
                where to begin on the management side. Without the right structures in place from day one, the risks
                were predictable: missed deadlines, scope creep, and a build that drifted from the start.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The approach">
              <p>
                Cyprusays brought us in to set the project up properly before development began. We started with
                discovery, working with the founders to understand the product, the offshore vendor relationship, and
                the constraints they were working within. The designs were already done, but no one had defined what
                success looked like, what was in scope, or how the build would actually be run.
              </p><br />
              <p>
                The first thing we did was create a formal project requirements document with clear success criteria, so
                the founders, the offshore vendor, and our team were all working from the same definition of success.
                From there, we built out the rest of the operating structure the team could carry forward themselves
                once we stepped back.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The solution">
              <p>
                With the requirements and success criteria locked in, we put the rest of the operating layer in place:
                roadmap, timelines, deadlines, review processes, decision logs, and a sensible delivery cadence. Beyond
                pure project management, we reviewed designs and flagged UX issues with significant downstream
                implications, advised on technical decisions that reshaped screen flows for the better, worked through
                user data storage and PII obligations, and guided the team through app store optimisation and launch
                positioning.
              </p><br />
              <p>
                We ran the project hands-on through roughly the first half of delivery, then handed the day-to-day to
                the founders, training them to manage the cadence themselves. We came back for the final stretch to
                support handover and launch.
              </p>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudySectionText title="The results">
              <p>
                There aren't growth metrics to share, because the value here was different. Cyprusays moved from a
                project drifting without direction to a confident in-house team capable of running their own delivery:
              </p>
              <CaseStudyResults
                results={[
                  {
                    title: 'Successful app launch on iOS and Android',
                    description: 'on time + on budget',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-solar'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'Empowered founders',
                    description: 'now running the project end to end themselves, with confidence and clarity',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-celestial'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'Subscriber base is growing',
                    description: '+ the business is tracking well',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-rosy'
                  },
                  {
                    title: 'Habits to keep delivering',
                    description:
                      'The team came away with the documentation, processes, and operating habits to keep delivering without external help',
                    backgroundColour: 'pixel-teal'
                  }
                ]}
              />

              <div class="mt-6 lg:mt-12"></div>

              <CaseStudyShout>
                For a founder-led start-up, the ability to own delivery end to end is the result that matters most.
              </CaseStudyShout>
            </CaseStudySectionText>

            <CaseStudyMetaData
              client={{ name: 'Cyprusays', url: 'https://www.cyprusays.com' }}
              industry={['Education', 'Community']}
              serviceNames={['Consulting']}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </Grid>
    </section>

    {/* Navigation section */}
    <CaseStudyNav
      previousCaseStudy={{ name: 'Previous case study', slug: 'previous-case-study' }}
      nextCaseStudy={{ name: 'Next case study', slug: 'next-case-study' }}
    />

    <ContactForm title="Discuss a similar challenge" displayDescription={false} />
  </article>

  <style>
    #case-study-page {
      --case-study-border: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-black) 8%, transparent);
      --case-study-placeholder: var(--color-pixel-placeholder-grey);
    }

    @media (max-width: 1023px) {
      .case-study-shell {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0;
        overflow: clip;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 240ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-left-pane {
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(-2rem);
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .case-study-right-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        overflow: clip;
        transform: translateX(2rem);
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 260ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-right-pane {
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        pointer-events: auto;
      }
    }

    @media (min-width: 1024px) {
      .case-study-shell {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0;
        transition: gap 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-shell {
        gap: 1.25rem;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane,
      .case-study-right-pane {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        transition:
          width 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          max-height 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
          opacity 260ms ease,
          transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
        will-change: width, max-height, opacity, transform;
      }

      .case-study-left-pane {
        width: 100%;
        max-height: 5000px;
      }

      .case-study-right-pane {
        width: 0;
        max-height: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(2rem);
        overflow: clip;
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-left-pane {
        width: calc(50% - 0.625rem);
      }

      #case-study-page[data-panel-state='open'] .case-study-right-pane {
        width: calc(50% - 0.625rem);
        max-height: 5000px;
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
        pointer-events: auto;
      }
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      .case-study-shell,
      .case-study-left-pane,
      .case-study-right-pane {
        transition: none;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    function initCaseStudyPage() {
      const page = document.getElementById('case-study-page')
      const toggle = document.getElementById('case-study-toggle')
      if (!(page instanceof HTMLElement) || !(toggle instanceof HTMLButtonElement)) return
      const pageElement = page
      const toggleButton = toggle

      const mobileMedia = window.matchMedia('(max-width: 1023px)')

      function setToggleTextColor() {
        const accent = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--accent-bgc').trim()
        const match = accent.match(/(\d+)\s*,\s*(\d+)\s*,\s*(\d+)/)
        if (!match) return

        let red = parseInt(match[1], 10) / 255
        let green = parseInt(match[2], 10) / 255
        let blue = parseInt(match[3], 10) / 255

        red = red <= 0.03928 ? red / 12.92 : Math.pow((red + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)
        green = green <= 0.03928 ? green / 12.92 : Math.pow((green + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)
        blue = blue <= 0.03928 ? blue / 12.92 : Math.pow((blue + 0.055) / 1.055, 2.4)

        const luminance = 0.2126 * red + 0.7152 * green + 0.0722 * blue
        document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--case-study-toggle-text', luminance > 0.4 ? '#000' : '#fff')
      }

      function getDefaultState() {
        return 'closed'
      }

      if (!pageElement.dataset.panelState) {
        pageElement.dataset.panelState = getDefaultState()
      }

      function syncA11y() {
        const isOpen = pageElement.dataset.panelState === 'open'
        toggleButton.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(isOpen))
      }

      setToggleTextColor()
      syncA11y()

      toggleButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
        pageElement.dataset.panelState = pageElement.dataset.panelState === 'open' ? 'closed' : 'open'
        syncA11y()
      })
    }

    initCaseStudyPage()
    document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', initCaseStudyPage)
  </script>
</Layout>
